# Maintenance Log API — Frontend

Base URL (local dev): `http://127.0.0.1:8000` — webpack proxies `/api/transcribe` and `/api/logs` to FastAPI. Production: set `LOG_API_BASE`.

All HTTP in `client/src/services/logService.ts`. TanStack Query in `client/src/hooks/logs/`.

## User flow

1. Stop recording → `POST /api/transcribe` → 202 `{ log_id, status: "transcribed", raw_text }`
2. Edit transcript → `PATCH /api/logs/:id` `{ raw_text }` → `POST /api/logs/:id/submit`
3. Poll `GET /api/logs/:id/status` every 1.5s until `status === "draft"` and `structured_data !== null`
4. Edit fields → `PUT /api/logs/:id` (all four fields required; use `""` if N/A)

## Status enum

| Status | FE action |
|--------|-----------|
| `transcribed` | Editable unstructured transcript + Submit |
| `pending` / `processing` | Poll status |
| `draft` | Structured form + Save & commit |
| `committed` | Success |
| `failed` | Show `error_message`, New log; stop polling |

Stop polling when: `status === "draft"` AND `structured_data !== null`, OR `status === "failed"`.

## Endpoints

| Method | Path | When |
|--------|------|------|
| POST | `/api/transcribe` | Stop recording; multipart `file`, optional `component_type` |
| PATCH | `/api/logs/:id` | Save edited `raw_text` before submit |
| POST | `/api/logs/:id/submit` | Submit for AI structuring |
| GET | `/api/logs/:id/status` | Poll after submit |
| PUT | `/api/logs/:id` | Commit when `draft` |

### Transcribe response (202)

```json
{ "log_id": "uuid", "status": "transcribed", "raw_text": "..." }
```

### Status response (200)

```json
{
  "id": "uuid",
  "status": "draft",
  "raw_text": "...",
  "structured_data": { "action": "", "part_number": "", "reference": "", "torque": "" },
  "error_message": null
}
```

### Commit body (PUT)

All four keys required: `action`, `part_number`, `reference`, `torque`.

## TypeScript (logService.ts)

- `StructuredLogData` — fixed four string fields
- `normalizeStructuredData()` — merge partial API data with `""` defaults
- `isLogStructuringComplete()` — `draft` + non-null `structured_data`
- `isLogFailed()` — `status === "failed"`
- `parseFastApiError()` — FastAPI `detail` string or array

## UI badges (LogCapturePage)

| Badge | Condition |
|-------|-----------|
| Recording | Mic active |
| Transcribing | ingest pending |
| Transcribed | has log_id, not submitted |
| Structuring | submitted, polling, not draft/failed |
| Drafted | structuring complete |
| Failed | `status === "failed"` |
| Committed | commit success |

## Errors

FastAPI: `{ "detail": "message" }` or validation array. Use `parseFastApiError`.
